All analyzed parameters meet the AB Tier 1 Guidelines with the exception of anthracene (0.009 mg/kg).
the flare stack.: All analyzed soil samples meet the AB Tier 1 Guidelines with the following exception: Anthracene (0.009 mg/kg)

WC: Soluble chloride concentrations were above AEP Tier 1 Guidelines for groundwater delineation. UST: SAR values in BH22-06 from 2.0 to 3.5 mbgs were
above the applicable rating category for subsoil at “Unsuitable”

Seventeen boreholes were advanced to identify and characterize a DWDA. The analytical results meet the AB Tier 1 Guidelines except for samples from three boreholes with one or more of pH, EC, SAR and hexavalent chromium
concentrations.

Based on field observations and analytical results collected during the assessment of the Site, salinity and PHC impacts are
present within the DWDA. Vertical and horizontal delineation was not achieved, and there is a minimum 500 m3 of
impacted material on site. A Record of Site Condition will be submitted using the Alberta Energy Regulator OneStop Tool
in conjunction with this report.

a substance release has occurred at the Site, as soluble chloride, EC and
SAR concentrations above criteria are present. The DWDA is interpreted to be present in BH22-06 and BH22-10, based on
analytical results.

a substance release has occurred at the Site, as soluble chloride, EC and
SAR concentrations above criteria are present. The DWDA is interpreted to be present in BH22-06 and BH22-10, based on
analytical results.

the ESA has
provided sufficient information to support that a substance release has occurred at the Site, as salinity, cobalt, arsenic,
and selenium impacts are present.

WC: Ethylbenzene, F1, F2, F3 impacts were identified. FP: Six boreholes were advanced near the Pit/Riser Area, to assess and delineate potential impacts.  Electrical conductivity (EC), Ethylbenzene, F1, F2, and F3 impacts were identified

ESA has
provided sufficient information to support that a substance release has occurred at the Site, as salinity impacts are present
in the potential on site DWDA.

All APECs passed except AST. Soil in the south process skid with AST and the riser area was not characterized for quality. Based on the findings of this Phase 2 ESA, soil samples in the APECs not assessed should be collected using hand methods,
in order for the Site to proceed to reclamation.

ESA has provided sufficient information to support that a substance release has occurred at the Site, as salinity impacts (soluble
chloride, SAR and EC) are present. Soluble chloride impacts are present in the northeast corner with an approximate area of 2.5 m × 2.5 m and a thickness of 1.5 m (0 to 1.5 mbgs). Additionally, there are impacts associated with the AST area with an approximate area of 15 m × 15 m and a thickness of 2.0 m (0 to 2.0 mbgs). The minimum calculated in-situ
soil volume is approximately 9.40 m3 and 450 m3 respectively.

The ESA has provided sufficient information to support that a substance release has occurred at the Site, as SAR exceedances are present within the well centre area.
